      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/2/28/8",
      "text": [
        " «إِنَّ ذَلِكَ فِي اَلْفَرِيضَةِ فَأَمَّا فِي اَلنَّافِلَةِ فَلَهُ أَنْ يُفْطِرَ أَيَّ سَاعَةٍ شَاءَ إِلَى غُرُوبِ اَلشَّمْسِ»."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.2002 - Sama‘ah asked Abu ‘Abd Allah (as) about the statement: \"The fasting person has the option until the sun passes its zenith.\"\nImam (as) replied: \"That applies to obligatory fasts. As for voluntary fasts, one may break the fast at any time they wish until sunset.\""
        ]
      }
